<document>
	<title>Management of major hemoptysis in patients with cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Schuster-S-R.</author>
	<author>Fellows-K-E.</author>

	<source>J-Pediatr-Surg. 1977 Dec. 12(6). P 889-96.</source>

	<abstract>Although bronchoscopy remains the best definitive method for
   localization of the site of hemorrhage in patients who have massive
   hemopytsis, angiography remains an important adjunct to this
   localization. When combined with embolization of the bleeding
   bronchial artery, it is an effective method of therapy for the
   management of massive hemoptysis in patients with cystic fibrosis.</abstract>

